{"_id":"A4dqWKiKYWtbHUwj","name":"Stalker, Scout & Drone Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.whKdtijyxztAwEDt"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"nOP1q3LkHfzMTS3E","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>HYPNOTIZING GAZE</b>: The Xeno morph, eyeless as it may seem, stares deeply into the soul of its victim. The victim is mesmerized by the dread beauty of such a beast. They stand in awe of what nature, or god, or the devil has created, get +1 STRESS LEVEL and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"jruKTIGoy1cnp684","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>PLAYING WITH ITS PREY</b>: The Xeno attacks, but not to kill. The target is knocked to the ground and drops all hand-held items, but otherwise takes no damage. The Xeno morph stands over them, taunting its prey to run so the game can go on. The victim gets +1 STRESS LEVEL and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"ahXgdHKV9YTmlMV6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DEADLY GRAB</b>: The beast launches through the air, grabbing its victim. It attacks with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If it hits it immediately drags them into a neighboring zone, dumping them on the floor. The victim is prone, drops all hand-held items and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"nZsGrO8mpGn15at6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>READY TO KILL</b>: The Xeno morph grabs its victim, its inner jaws poised to strike. Roll for the attack with ten Base Dice. If it hits, the victim counts as grabbed (see page 93) and needs to make an opposed CLOSE COMBAT roll against ten Base Dice to break loose. The victim and all friendly characters in the same zone must make Panic Rolls. Unless the victim breaks free, the Xeno morph will use a HEADBITE attack against them on its next initiative.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"raN4TNJml4ER1WuU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>CAPTURE FOR THE HIVE</b>: The Xeno morph attacks with its venom-spiked tail, with ten Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes any damage, the Xeno pulls its punch so only one point of damage is inflicted, and the paralyzing venom takes effect. The victim must make a STAMINA roll—the number of success rolled is the number of Rounds they can stay up, then they fall unconscious for one Shift. The paralysis can be removed with a shot of adrenaline (a MEDICAL AID roll using a Medkit).","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"c1LER6xJ3D2CxqCg","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>HEADBITE</b>: The Xeno morph opens its outer jaws wide, and the deadly inner jaws lean out, gnashing in anticipation before snapping forwards. The attack has a strength of nine Base Dice, Damage 2. If it causes any damage it automatically inflicts critical injury #64, killing the victim in one dreadful blow. However, should the GM wish it, the victim remains just alive enough for the Xeno morph to initiate the ovomorphing process.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":true}
{"_id":"F7TmkOFn2VhGHrL5","name":"Abomination Attacks (Stage III and IV)","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.8hDJUZRR0NzCgIhq"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"3CLLNxWv4Y9FpvRh","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>HORRIBLE ROAR</b> The Abomination screams in fury. All humans in SHORT range must make an immediate panic roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"EjgxTewuN46OM7IW","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>FIST STRIKE</b> The Abomination strikes its victim with a powerful punch. Roll for the attack with ten Base Dice, Damage 1.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"gO8Frde9tPRtEjKw","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>THROW</b> The Abomination grabs the victim and tries to slam it into the nearest hard surface. Roll for the attack using nine Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the victim lands prone at SHORT range from the Abomination, drops any hand-held items, and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"AZqOc1lRmZpneuGD","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>POUNCE</b> The Abomination leaps onto its victim like a big monkey. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack hits, the victim is knocked to the ground, drops any hand-held items, and must make an immediate Panic Roll. The Abomination then starts pounding the victim with its powerful fists. This is resolved as an immediate bonus attack with twelve Base Dice, Damage 2.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"PKUCgS1WmfxONUA6","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>ARM PULL</b> The Abomination grabs the victim’s arm and tries to pull it clean off with its bare hands. Roll for the attack using six Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically triggers critical injury #54 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"eGWoRnsVc3fVMUXf","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>HEAD CRUSH</b> The Abomination grabs the victim’s head and tries to crush it with its bare hands. Roll for the attack using seven Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically triggers critical injury #64 (even if the victim is not Broken), killing the victim outright.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false}
{"_id":"rhCQMdGbBSyfMnq3","name":"Neomorph Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.zYwiwLxGMdhxypqA"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"TgqnLN359aAe3PGM","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>TERRIFYING HISS</b> The Neomorph leans in close to the victim, showing its razor-sharp teeth and hissing. The victim must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,1],"drawn":false},{"_id":"MZCcP9qVpwWpHiQK","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>TAIL SLASH</b> The Neomorph pivots, slashing its victim with its sharp tail. The victim is at- tacked using ten Base Dice, Damage 2. The attack is armor piercing, halving any Armor Rating.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[2,2],"drawn":false},{"_id":"YnrHp1Voqm1RklLU","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>DEADLY GRAB</b> The Neomorph jumps at its victim, grabbing it and dragging it away. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If it hits, the Neomorph immediately drags the victim into the next zone ( MEDIUM range) before releasing it. The victim falls prone, drops any hand-held items, and must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[3,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"HuvLUgmBYjLePf88","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>LEAPING ATTACK</b> The Neomorph jumps at the victim. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack is successful, the victim is thrown to the ground and must make an immediate Panic Roll, and the Neomorph immediately performs an extra attack with ten Base Dice, Damage 2 (does not count as an action). The extra attack cannot be blocked.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"wAoGhAz5ZVlQkFCr","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>THROAT BITE</b> The Neomorph bites the victim’s throat. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #61 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"auXwyeSs7hrWDZpV","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>TAIL SPIKE</b> The Neomorph impales the victim with its razor-sharp tail. Roll for the attack using seven Base Dice, Damage 1. The attack is armor piercing, halving any Armor Rating. If the attack causes damage, it automatically triggers critical injury #66 (even if the victim is not Broken), killing the victim outright.d","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false}
{"_id":"yGpErOWutoDi7K72","name":"Bloodburster Attacks","permission":{"default":0,"q8HmJQOf882klbgH":3},"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"RollTable.NoBY37kUmuyydbNC"}},"img":"icons/svg/d20-grey.svg","description":"","results":[{"_id":"tpydHGtYWxajvhAy","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>ESCAPE</b> With a snarl, the Bloodburster flees, moving two zones away in a single action, into the nearest air duct if possible. As soon as the PCs lose line of sight, combat ends and stealth mode ensues. After D6 Turns, the Bloodburster grows into a Juvenile Neomorph and starts stalking the PCs.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[1,3],"drawn":false},{"_id":"9cwsYxHURRBFLDed","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>TERRIFYING HISS</b> The Bloodburster jumps onto the victim, showing its razor-sharp teeth and hissing. The victim must make an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[4,4],"drawn":false},{"_id":"fsKDB5gcKkI9yeac","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>LEG BITE</b> With a snarl, the Bloodburster bites the victim’s leg. Roll for the attack using six Base Dice, Damage 2. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #53 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[5,5],"drawn":false},{"_id":"LA1yh9jeiG7vdv0y","flags":{},"type":0,"text":"<b>THROAT BITE</b> The Bloodburster bites the victim’s throat. Roll for the attack using eight Base Dice, Damage 1. If the attack causes damage, it automatically inflicts critical injury #61 (even if the victim is not Broken), triggering an immediate Panic Roll.","img":"icons/svg/d20-black.svg","resultId":"","weight":1,"range":[6,6],"drawn":false}],"formula":"1d6","replacement":true,"displayRoll":false}
